y Magazine,'' March 1923.\n* [http://www.unz.org/Pub/Century-1923may-00034 \"The Game of Psychoanalysis,\"] ''The Century Magazine,'' May 1923.\n* [https://archive.org/stream/essaysoftoday00prituoft#page/226/mode/2up \"A Defense of Detective Stories.\"] In: ''Essays of Today,'' George G. Harrap & Co., 1923.\n* [http://www.unz.org/Pub/LivingAge-1925jun06-00529 \"The World State,\"] ''The Living Age,'' June 1925.\n* [http://www.unz.org/Pub/Forum-1926jan-00031 \"Why I Am a Catholic,\"] ''The Forum,'' January 1926.\n* [http://www.unz.org/Pub/Forum-1928jun-00801 \"The International Irritant,\"] ''The Forum,'' June 1928.\n* [http://www.unz.org/Pub/Forum-1929feb-00065 \"The Skeptic as a Critic,\"] ''The Forum,'' February 1929.\n* [http://www.unz.org/Pub/Bookman-1929may-00236 \"Is Humanism a Religion?,\"] ''The Bookman,'' May 1929.\n* [http://www.unz.org/Pub/Forum-1929jun-00360 \"The West\u2019s Defense,\"] ''The Forum,'' June 1929.\n* [http://www.unz.org/Pub/NorthAmericanRev-1929oct-00435 \"The Doom of the Darnaways,\"] ''The North American Review,'' Vol. 228, No. 4, Oct. 1929.\n* [http://www.unz.org/Pub/NorthAmericanRev-1929nov-00587 \"The Inefficiency of Science,\"] ''The North American Review,'' Vol. 228, No. 5, Nov. 1929.\n* [http://www.unz.org/Pub/Bookman-1930mar-00027 \"Magic and Fantasy in Fiction,\"] ''The Bookman,'' March 1930.\n* [http://www.unz.org/Pub/LivingAge-1930jul15-00616 \"Keeping up with Mr. Shaw,\"] ''The Living Age,'' July 1930.\n* [http://www.unz.org/Pub/Bookman-1930oct-00097 \"The Spirit of the Age in Literature,\"] ''The Bookman,'' October 1930.\n* [http://www.unz.org/Pub/Forum-1931oct-00224 \"Reflections on a Rotten Apple,\"] ''The Forum,'' October 1931.\n* \"The Mission of Ireland,\" ''Studies: An Irish Quarterly Review,'' Vol. 21, No. 83, Sep. 1932.\n* [http://www.unz.org/Pub/Bookman-1932dec-00807 \"The End of the Moderns,\"] ''The Bookman,'' December 1932 Rep. in ''The American Conservative''.\n* [http://www.unz.org/Pub/AmericanRev-1933apr-00076